headline: Moderna Stock Is Climbing on Trial Data. A Flu-Covid Vaccine Isn’t a Sure Thing.
summary: An influenza vaccine candidate from  Moderna  showed promising results in a late-stage trial, bringing the drug maker one step closer to producing a combined flu-and-Covid shot.  Moderna  said its seasonal flu vaccine candidate, mRNA-1010, showed “positive results” in a Phase 3 efficacy study comparing it with a licensed standard-dose seasonal flu vaccine.  In participants aged 65 years and older, mRNA-1010 had a relative vaccine efficacy rate of 27.4%, Moderna said.
